subSubSection.paragraph:
Head transverse, approximately 1.05-1.15 times as wide as long (
Fig. 85
); punctation fine, shallow, and moderately dense; interstices with micropunctation of variable density; eyes large and more or less strongly convex, approximately twice as long as postocular region in dorsal view or longer. Antennae short; antennomere III slightly shorter than II; IV moderately transverse; V-X of gradually increasing width and increasingly transverse; X almost twice as wide as long (
Fig. 86
).

